            “the king is helpless,” evolved into “checkmate.”
          </p>
          <p>
            Shatranj emphasized strategic depth, introducing key concepts like the opening, middlegame, and endgame.
            This period marked chess's transformation from a war simulation to an intellectual pursuit, becoming a
